05:48.515 --> 05:50.757
All right, I'm calling Sheila
and then Robert and...

05:50.851 --> 05:53.013
You're not calling
anyone, Gretchen.

05:53.103 --> 05:54.264
I don't want Robert to know.

05:54.354 --> 05:55.890
You have to tell him
what happened.

05:55.981 --> 05:57.267
I can't.

05:58.316 --> 06:00.808
- Why not?
- Because he's my new managing partner,

06:00.902 --> 06:02.814
and I do not want him
to know that I am weak.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.736
Louis, you are not weak.

06:04.906 --> 06:06.926
It could have happened to anybody.
It could have happened to him.

06:06.950 --> 06:08.052
Yeah, but it didn't.
It happened to me,

06:08.076 --> 06:09.220
and that's why
I don't want to tell him.

06:09.244 --> 06:10.324
Well, what are you
gonna do?

06:10.370 --> 06:11.472
'Cause he's gonna wanna know

06:11.496 --> 06:12.682
why you didn't show up
to that meeting.

06:12.706 --> 06:15.073
I'm going to let him think
what he already thinks.

06:15.166 --> 06:16.644
That Sheila and I,
we're trying to have a child,

06:16.668 --> 06:18.145
- it took longer than we thought...
- Louis.

06:18.169 --> 06:19.660
Gretchen, I'm done
talking about this.

06:19.754 --> 06:21.791
So will you just please
let me be?

06:21.882 --> 06:23.999
Okay, Louis,
I won't tell anybody.

06:24.134 --> 06:26.342
I'm not going anywhere
until we patch you up.

06:38.398 --> 06:40.209
If you're not careful,
the bagel guy's going to figure out

06:40.233 --> 06:41.314
you're cheating on him.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.687
Who says
this isn't a bagel?

06:42.777 --> 06:45.381
Same person who says you've got
the sense of humor of a 5-year-old.

06:45.405 --> 06:47.567
I am so going to pull
your pigtails at recess.

06:47.657 --> 06:48.898
Okay, do you want
to keep going,

06:48.992 --> 06:50.574
or can I ask you
a serious question?

06:50.869 --> 06:52.155
- You want the truth?
- No.

06:52.454 --> 06:54.867
I want to talk to you
about doing more pro bonos.

06:55.665 --> 06:56.997
- Donna.
- Harvey, listen to me.

06:57.083 --> 06:59.291
That cleaning woman's case
was good for you,

06:59.377 --> 07:01.164
and even though
Mike's not here,

07:01.254 --> 07:02.398
I think we should
keep doing them.

07:02.422 --> 07:04.709
Donna, I might be missing Mike,
but I'm not Mike,

07:04.799 --> 07:06.335
and I have a meeting
in an hour.

07:06.426 --> 07:08.713
But if you want to take on a pro bono,
knock yourself out.

07:08.803 --> 07:09.964
You know what, I do,

07:10.055 --> 07:11.449
and if you don't want it,
I'm just going to go ask Alex.

07:11.473 --> 07:14.090
- Not Alex. He's not in the mood.
- Why not?

07:14.225 --> 07:15.466
He found out
about Zane

07:15.560 --> 07:17.204
promising Samantha
name partner last night.

07:17.228 --> 07:18.435
What did you say to him?

07:18.563 --> 07:20.333
What do you think I said?
I told him to sit tight.

07:20.357 --> 07:22.168
Did you sit tight when you were
in the same position?

07:22.192 --> 07:23.603
That's what he said.

07:23.693 --> 07:25.171
Then if you don't want him doing
what you did,

07:25.195 --> 07:27.187
which is go looking
for another job,

07:27.280 --> 07:28.466
then I suggest
you do something

07:28.490 --> 07:29.731
that makes him want to stay.

07:31.201 --> 07:34.160
Now, I'm going to go ask Katrina
if she wants to do a pro bono.

07:38.416 --> 07:39.827
I don't care what it takes.

07:39.918 --> 07:41.020
You get him
in front of that judge,

07:41.044 --> 07:42.626
I'll get him off the hook.

07:42.754 --> 07:43.790
Good.

07:44.631 --> 07:46.609
Whatever you're cooking,
I need you to bump this class action

07:46.633 --> 07:47.669
to the front of the line.

07:47.759 --> 07:48.920
Class action?

07:49.010 --> 07:50.546
Yeah, why?
You got a problem with that?

07:50.637 --> 07:53.846
No problem, but litigation isn't
my specialty and you know it.

07:53.932 --> 07:55.093
So what's going on?

07:55.183 --> 07:56.219
What's going on is

07:56.309 --> 07:58.221
this was Louis Litt's case
and now it's yours.

07:58.311 --> 07:59.747
And how does
Louis Litt feel about that?

07:59.771 --> 08:01.207
I don't give a shit
about how he feels.

08:01.231 --> 08:02.267
Well, I do.

08:02.899 --> 08:04.435
I just got on
good footing around here,

08:04.526 --> 08:05.670
I'm not looking
to undo it. Now I got...

08:05.694 --> 08:08.402
Hold on, now.
You are my go-to.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.128
Don't start playing
office politics on me.

08:10.198 --> 08:11.814
Robert, I played
office politics

08:11.908 --> 08:13.865
for you for years,
in case you forgot.

08:14.035 --> 08:16.072
I didn't, but the man
pulled a no-show

08:16.162 --> 08:17.653
to a meeting
with his own client.

08:17.747 --> 08:20.956
And I need to send a message.
So are you in or out?

08:22.752 --> 08:24.994
Okay, Robert. I'm in.

08:31.594 --> 08:33.631
I'm sure whatever it is
is very important, Harvey,

08:33.763 --> 08:35.004
but I'm a little busy
right now.

08:35.097 --> 08:36.464
Alex, you were right.

08:36.890 --> 08:38.369
If I were in your shoes,
sitting tight

08:38.393 --> 08:39.679
wouldn't fly with me
either.

08:39.936 --> 08:41.518
I thought about it,
and I got an idea.

08:41.604 --> 08:42.789
Well, if it isn't
you and Louis

08:42.813 --> 08:44.350
telling Zane
my number's up next,

08:44.441 --> 08:45.761
I'm not sure
I'm going to like it.

08:45.817 --> 08:47.774
What it is,
is you doing something

08:47.861 --> 08:49.818
to put you on the map
with Zane.

08:54.951 --> 08:56.192
Paxson BioScience.

08:56.286 --> 08:57.743
They're big,
they're juicy,

08:57.829 --> 08:59.786
and we got a meeting
with them in a half an hour.

08:59.873 --> 09:01.330
- We?
- Yeah, we.

09:01.416 --> 09:02.873
Then forget it.

09:02.959 --> 09:05.187
